                  <summary><title>Haft iqlīm</title> by Amīn Aḥmad Rāzī, a collection of biographical and
                     topographical entries arranged in order of the seven climes (<hi rend="italic">iqlīm</hi>)</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4541-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied"
                           key="ark:/81055/vdc_100166176941.0x000001 viaf_34425337">Amīn Aḥmad
                           Rāzī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied"
                           key="ark:/81055/vdc_100166176941.0x000001 viaf_34425337">امين احمد
                           رازى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_2157">Haft iqlīm</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_2157">هفت اقليم</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>The date in the colophon reads سنه ۱۰۶ which most likely represents
                           regnal year 16 (1663-64) of the Emperor Aurangzeb, where the middle digit
                           represents the 'n' of <hi rend="italic">sanah</hi>, though it could be
                           interpreted as [1]106 (1694-95), or even 106[0] (1650).</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc form="codex">
                     <supportDesc material="chart">
                        <extent>525 ff.<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
                              <height>328</height>
                              <width>180</width>
                           </dimensions>
                           <dimensions type="written" unit="mm"/>
                        </extent>
                     </supportDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote script="Arabic" scope="major">Nastaʻlīq; copied in black ink, with
                        headings and overlinings in red; catchwords</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote type="headpiece">Illuminated polychrome headpiece (<locus>f.
                           1v</locus>). </decoNote>
                     <decoNote>Interlinear and marginal gilding (<locus>ff 1v-2r</locus>); ruled
                        text-frames. </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <p>The names of countries, towns and persons dealt with in the text have in
                        many cases been written marginally by <persName role="ann"
                           key="viaf_29651479">E. G Browne</persName>, with a few pencillings by
                           <persName role="ann" key="viaf_20430079">Major H.G. Raverty</persName>. </p>
                     <p>Notes on f. 1r give a date of purchase, accompanied by his rectangular seal,
                        by <persName role="fmo" key="">Muḥammad Aḥsan Allāh Khān</persName> on 15
                        Rabiʻ I, RY 3 of Ahmad Shah (1164, 11 Feb 1751) from the book-binder (<hi
                           rend="italic">ṣaḥḥāf</hi>) <persName role="bnd" key="">Muhammad
                           ʻAlī</persName>. </p>
                     <p>Other former owners mentioned are <persName role="fmo" key="">Allāh Sayyid
                           Muḥammad</persName> and <persName role="fmo" key="">Mīrzā Muḥammad
                           Khiṣāl</persName></p>. <p>A valuation of Rs 52 is given alongside an
                        inspection dated 22 Shavval in regnal year 24 of an unspecified ruler.</p>
                     <p>Partially covered over accession statements in Persian by <persName
                           xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_287207857" role="fmo">Richard
                           Johnson</persName> (or his <hi rend="italic">munshi</hi>), record that
                        the manuscript was purchased for Rs 30 and accessioned on 10 Rajab of an
                        unspecified year: <hi rend="italic">[Kitāb-i Sarkār] Navvāb Ṣāḥib Mumtāz
                           al-Dawlah Mufakhkhar al-Mulk Ḥusām Jang [Mistar Richārd] Jānsan Ṣāḥib
                           Bahādur dām iqbāluh. Kitāb-i Haft iqlīm kharīd sī rūpīyah ba-tārīkh-i
                           dahum shahr-i Rajab dākhil-i kitābkhānah shud.</hi></p><p/>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding notBefore="1800" notAfter="1899">
